The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 March is 40,360 (4,671.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 February, there were 566 new confirmed cases (65.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 February, there were 748 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (182 fewer cases).
